      "text": "The Lockwood Estate is a large mansion located in the mountains of Colorado Springs, Colorado. The house was built by the family's ancestor, Sigmund Lockwood, in 1885. The house is surrounded by a large garden which is surrounded by tall shrubbery. There are many books in the library, which is hidden behind a secret door in the fireplace of Christopher's Study. Aston discovered this hidden room by accident two months after his uncle's disappearance. \nThe main room in the house is shaped like an oval with pillars around the periphery supporting an indoor balcony that gives guests access to various bedrooms and a billiards room. A large staircase goes from the main atrium up to the second floor where the balcony is. A small wet bar is positioned to the side of the main room for refreshments. ",
