      "text": "The Columbia University Library is the largest university library in the United States. It was founded in 1865 and contains millions of books and documents. It is located in New York City, and is open to the public. The library's collection contains rare books, manuscripts, and other historical documents. The library also houses the largest collection of rare books in the world. The library has many treasures, including 9,000 volumes of ancient Greek art, a rare copy of an Ancient Egyptian papyrus, a Gutenberg Bible, and a Gutenberg Bible facsimile. It also has a very rare Gutenberg Bible, which was first printed in 1455. The library also has a set of very rare maps, including a set of maps from the Library of Congress. The set was last used by Abraham Lincoln for his famous Gettysburg Address. The library also has some very rare books, including a set of books by Ernest Hemingway and a set of 19th Century scientific books.\nThe library was founded by John Jay, who was a student at Columbia at the time. He donated over 10 million dollars to buy books for the library.",
