      "text": "The smoke in the crowded room was thicker and somehow heavier than the room was full. From his shaded booth in the corner, conveniently positioned to command a clear view of the room he could clearly hear and see the two men talking quietly at the dimly lit bar. He leaned forward, taking another sip, savoring the expensive glass of pinot, and subtly looked passed the taller of the two towards the bartender. The older one was packing. He could see how the leather bulged where the beretta was tucked into the back of his trousers. “Elmo” Maria Marconi pretended to read the newspaper but all he could think about was the ten thousand Lira sitting in the briefcase at his feet. It got heavier as the seconds ticked by and he could feel the little bead of perspiration begin forming on his furrowed brow. His watch said a quarter to seven. It would be soon. ",
