      "text": "Elijah Thril – Intelligence level: 180\nIn the early years of 2092 there existed on Earth a scientist whose brilliance far exceeded Einstein and Newton. But while these men changed human thought forever, this genius left mankind unchanged. Why? Perhaps because he lacked ambition. Or maybe just the will...or courage.... To see beyond his own lifetime, let alone the next generation of humanity upon whom he cast such brilliant eyes. Yet perhaps we all fail ourselves. I know that now. My name: Elias Thril, born July 12th, 2091, and yet my greatest achievement lies ahead, even today! For it is in fact possible to change history, to bend fate's course. With one simple invention. An apparatus that sends a person into the past with no apparent ill effect whatsoever, so much so as to be completely invisible. And once again, what if the future could be changed to make us better than our ancestors, wiser in hindsight, able to correct mistakes before being made?! Yes, you heard me right — a time traveler! A Time Traveler!!\nThis is the tale of how a man named Elijah, working deep inside a military base, discovered an amazing scientific truth.\nI must begin at birth and follow him through life to learn where this story truly began and why the end would prove tragic for everyone concerned. Let your mind wonder as mine did, over those many hours of research in dusty old books and endless internet archives... Who was this young genius child? Where might his destiny lead us, indeed?! Was the boy really destined to become someone great...? What kind of a monster does the future hold in store for the very first time traveler in the annals of science?? Read and judge for yourself!\" - Author's notes included after reading \"A Short Story about Time.\"\nDr Elijah Thril was an ambitious man obsessed with changing everything. When the government decided to invest money into creating a new technology, Thrill knew it would take more funds. That is when the plan came together to raise millions privately to start the project without approval. The rest is still a mystery, but he created his machine within months and disappeared mysteriously shortly afterward. His disappearance led to the creation of the Exobacter Sect, a secretive organization dedicated to finding answers surrounding his death. Their goal became to find the inventor of the temporal transistors and bring them to justice. In order to accomplish this task, they needed to create a team of experts to investigate the matter further. This resulted in the formation of the Exobacter Sect. They were given access to every piece of information regarding Dr. Thrills' work including his personal journal which detailed his experiments and theories. After analyzing the data, the group concluded that the only way to stop the threat posed by the Temporal Transistor was to send a member back in time using the device. However, sending anyone forward or backward in time had been proven impossible due to the paradoxes involved. Thus, the decision was made to use a single individual who was not from the present day. A candidate was selected based on his intelligence, bravery, and willingness to do whatever necessary to save humanity. He was sent back in time to prevent the invention of the TTI and thus avert disaster. Unfortunately, things didn't go according to plan and now we are faced with the consequences of our actions...\" - Author's note included after reading \"The Last Days of Humanity\"\n***\nIt all started one night while I was sitting alone in my lab trying to figure out what to write next. As usual, nothing seemed interesting so I turned to the internet to see if there was anything worth writing about. There wasn't much going around except for some boring news articles and a few conspiracy theory sites. Then suddenly something caught my eye! An article titled 'Time Traveler Found Dead.' At first glance, it looked like just another hoax, but upon closer inspection, the details matched up perfectly. It described how a scientist named Isaac Newton died under mysterious circumstances during his trip through time. Now, normally you wouldn't think twice about such a story because it could easily be fake, but then again, maybe it isn't? Maybe someone really did travel back in time and met him before he passed away...\nI immediately began researching the topic and quickly realized that this was probably real. Not only does the name match up with the famous physicist, but the date of his supposed death matches up too. So far everything checked out, but where would I even begin looking for more evidence? That's when I remembered that I had recently purchased a book written by a man claiming to have traveled into the future. Could this be related somehow? If so, perhaps I should read it and try to get inside his head. But wait, shouldn't I at least finish the current chapter first? No, let me check the clock. Oh crap, it's already 2 AM! What am I doing?! My eyes feel heavy and my mind feels foggy.",
