      "text": "Somewhere on the Atlantic, Between New York City and Portsmouth, 1887\nIt was late evening by the time the three men reached their destination. After having traveled through two countries, crossing multiple rivers, walking miles upon end, and battling against nature itself, they finally arrived at a small fishing village located near the southern coast of England. The sun was beginning its descent into the ocean, painting everything orange. It cast shadows along the cliffs surrounding the bay. On the beach, the water looked blacker than normal due to the low sunlight reflecting off of it. As if in answer to the sunset, a lone seagull circled above the town square below. Its wings flapped loudly, causing the wind to whip sand across the cobblestone streets. In front of the church stood a large sign reading: 'Welcome to Bournemouth.' Below that, written in chalk, read the words, 'Beware the Devil's Footprints!'. Rupert Macintosh, Hax Lud, and Temple Sexton made their debut on the town in style. Their clothes were new and clean; their faces were freshly shaved and oiled. All three men had taken great pains to appear presentable. This was important because there would likely be some who might recognize them, which could lead to trouble. Not only were these individuals from faraway places, but they also held positions of power. To make matters worse, all three men carried guns—not just any kind either. These weapons were custom-made by none other than the infamous John Moses Browning himself. Each gun bore serial numbers stamped into the barrel and frame, indicating they were among the first manufactured.",
