      "text": "Hugo stood staring out the window overlooking their property which spanned hundreds of acres outside Denver. There wasn't another house nearby or anywhere within sight. The most prominent feature nearest them was the bulky silhouette of Mount Evans. Even though he lived here, Hugo felt disconnected from everything. The rain was coming. Heavy drops fell on the glass panes, making it difficult to see beyond the thick curtains covering all windows throughout the estate. Raindrops clung tightly to the plants growing along the perimeter wall and dripped down onto the stone walkway below. Above the clouds hung heavy gray skies above the mountain peaks. In some places, snow lingered atop the higher elevations. After several minutes of silence, Hugo finally spoke without looking away from the scene through the foggy pane.\n\"It'll start soon.\"",
