tioned. This tends to corroborate in a general way the \nview argued in my previous book Reich of the Black Sun that the Germans may have used some type of weapon of mass destruction \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nduring their military operations on the Eastern Front. \n\n372 \n\nBearden, “Historical Background of Scalar EM Weapons,” Analysis of Scalar/Electromagnetic Technology (Tesla Book Company), \n\np. 12. \n\n373 \n\nBearden, Fer tie Lance: Briefing on Soviet Scalar Electromagnetic Weapons^ Cheniere, 2002), p. 6. Bearden offers no source for the \nquotation. \n\n374 \n\nBearden, “Historical Background of Scalar EM Weapons,” Analysis of Scalar/Electromagnetic Technology (Tesla Book Company), \n\np. 12. \n\n375 \n\nBearden, Fer De Lance: Briefing on Soviet Scalar Electromagnetic Weapons^ Santa Barbada, California: Cheniere Press, 2002), p. \n\n7. \n\n376 \nIbid. \n\n377 \n\nStrictly speaking, “zero point energy” and “quantum potential” are not the same thing, even though the terms tend to be used \nindiscriminately even by physicists to indicate the energy of the medium or vacuum. \n\n378 \n\nBearden, Energy from the Vacuum: Concepts and Print iples(C heniere, 2002), p. xx, italicized emphasis mine, bold and italicized \nemphasis Bearden’s. \n\n379 \n\nBearden, Fer De Lance, pp. 6-7, n. 5. \n\n380 \n\nBearden, Energy from the Vacuum, p. xxii, emphasis added. \n\n381 \n\nIbid., p. 584. Bearden calls this statement “the central message” of his long and quite technical tome. \n\n382 \n\nQ.v. Energy from the Vacuum., pp. 22-23, for some disturbing questions and implications of this insight. \n\n383 \n\nJoseph P. Farrell, Reich of the Black Sun. pp. 226-228. \n\n384 \n\nBearden, Energy from the Vacuum, p. xix. Note that Bearden is implying something quite different from Special or General \nRelativity: a local curvature or dynamic of space that is engineerable. \n\n385 \n\nFor a rigorous discussion of the standard versus “scalar” definitions of closed and open systems in thermodynamics, see Bearden, \nEnergy from the Vacuum, p. 6, n. 9. See also Fer De Lance, pp. 110-111. \n\n386 \n\nBearden notes that “the fact that general relativity falsified much of the present foundations of classical thermodynamics seems to \nhave been either ignored or missed by most of the scientific community, although we still (are able to) quote leading Russian \nscientists who have noticed it and are aware of it.” (Energy from the Vacuum, p. 7.) \n\n387 \n\nE.T. Whittaker, “On the partial differential equations of mathematical physics,” Mathematische Annalen, Vol 57, 1903 (333-355), p. \n355, italicized emphasis mine, bold and italicized emphasis Whittaker’s. \n\n388 \n\nBearden, “Maxwell’s Original Quaternion Theory was a Unified Field Theory of Electromagnetics and Gravitation,” Proceedings oj \nthe international Tesla Society, 6/24-6/68, p. 6/24. \n\n389 \n\nBearden. Energy from the Vacuum, p. 145, bold and italicized emphasis Bearden’s, italicized emphasis mine. \n\n390 \n\nBearden, Fer De Lance, p. 27. For more on CSRs, see pp. 15-16. \n\n391 \n\nIbid., p. 112, bold and italicized emphasis Bearden’s, italicized emphasis mine. \n\n392 \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nIbid., p. 173. \n\n393 \n\n\nI am acutely aware of over-simplifying so much of Bearden’s (and others’) thinking here. \n\n394 \n\nBearden, Energy from the Vacuum, p. 244. \n\n395 \n\nBearden, Fer De Lance., p. 209. \n\n396 \n\nIbid., pp. 209-210, emphasis added. Readers of my Giza Death Star trilogy will recall that I indicated that one characteristic of a \nscalar weapon of “mass destruction” planet-busting potential was precisely that it be coupled to the base solar system that it is in. \nQ.v. my Giza Death Star, pp. 251-252. The reason for this requirement, once again, is that large masses are natural resonators to \nscalar waves. \n\n397 \n\nSee my Giza Death StarDeployed, Giza Death Star Destroyed. \n\n398 \n\nBearden, Fer De Lance, p. 408, emphasis is 